{
  "stem": "9156.8",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then one time in the child guidance clinic-- I think it's 1945-- when I worked with the children, that was done in the basement, I fell on my head, and I got a retina detachment, which means that you get blind.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And this is-- as far as I know, I was the first or second person where the retina attachment worked.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But it was very different when they-- four weeks immobilized in a hospital.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And there are all kinds of stories.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But I have to say, my colleagues would come day after day and-- talk about American kindness.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You know, they would come and be there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Meanwhile, somebody had notified the Red Cross.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I think it's 19-- the end of the war is in '45, isn't it?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I forgot which month.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's before the end of the war that Paul gets to get back to the United States.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so he came back, and I was still not seeing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had to always live with something black in front, and little-- not very easy.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "All kinds of stuff.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I have knitted a whole thing with being blind.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I'm very proud of that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But anyhow, I, meanwhile, had been speaking all across everywhere, mostly on what my whole life is about.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "About-- to give dignity to every human being, but also about children and young people that I care about.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I came once to speak in Minneapolis.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's before Paul came back.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And at the University, they invited me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I had no idea, but I didn't know-- they were looking me over, but I didn't know that.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So once I wrote at that time to Paul that the two most beautiful places I had seen in the United States were San Francisco and Minneapolis.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
